types of cones:</font></font> <font face="Arial,Helvetica"><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="6"><a href="cone-types.pdf"><img src="../../../Graphics%20Templates/Diamonds/Di-red.gif" alt="The linked PDF file shows the three cone types that are responsible for the perception of the primary colors red, blue and green." border="0" height="11" width="11"></a></font></font> 
</p><ul> <li> <font face="Arial,Helvetica"><font size="+2">red-sensitive: 64%, high 
concentration in fovea area</font></font></li><li> <font face="Arial,Helvetica"><font size="+2">green-sensitive: 
32%, high concentration in fovea area</font></font></li><li> <font face="Arial,Helvetica"><font size="+2">blue-sensitive: 
2%, evenly distributed over retina; none in the center of the fovea.</font></font></li></ul><br>&nbsp; 
